text: Bo (Bosse) Johan Edvard Magnus Johnsson (Bo Irvall) (5 September 1902 - 29 July 1981) was a Swedish swimmer. He competed in the men's 200 metre breaststroke event at the 1924 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1902 births Category:1981 deaths Category:Swedish male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Sweden Category:Swimmers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:People from Falun Category:Swedish male breaststroke swimmers
